        <div class="topic">
        <h2>What is Stealing?</h2>
        <p>Stealing is the act of taking something that doesn’t belong to you without permission. It can involve physical items, digital assets, or even ideas. While it may seem harmless to some, stealing can have serious consequences for everyone involved.</p>

        <h2>The Consequences of Stealing</h2>
          <div class="topic">
        <ul>
          <li>Legal consequences stealing is a crime that can lead to arrest, fines, and even jail time.</li>
          <li>Harming relationships theft can break trust between friends, family, and coworkers.</li>
          <li>The impact on society When people steal, leads to higher costs for everyone, including businesses and consumers.</li>
          <li>Personal Impact Individuals who steal usually have feelings of guilt, shame, and regret.</li>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <h2>Why Should We Care?</h2>
          <div class="topic">
        <p>Stealing isn’t just a personal issue it affects the entire community. It creates a lot of distrust and fear. By choosing to respect others property and follow the law, we can build stronger, safer communities where everyone can thrive.</p>
          </div>
        <h2>What Can You Do?</h2>
          <div class="topic">
        <p>Start by making a effort to value honesty, respect,when you are affecting others, encourage your peers to do the same. Small actions can lead to big changes.</p>
          </div>
